1
00:00:03,160 --> 00:00:04,840
Okay, I can't talk right now,
I'm driving. Bye.

2
00:00:06,200 --> 00:00:09,040
What do you mean? Rotem's mom
told me the teacher yelled at me today?

3
00:00:09,560 --> 00:00:11,120
Yeah, today when I picked up the kid.

4
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:13,400
Why, what happened?
-Just, I was a bit late.

5
00:00:14,320 --> 00:00:18,400
Oh, how late is "a bit" today?
-Five, six minutes.

6
00:00:18,840 --> 00:00:21,000
It was super busy at the turn by the traffic light.

7
00:00:21,120 --> 00:00:23,120
The teacher said you're a liar.

8
00:00:23,240 --> 00:00:26,440
Dads aren't called liars.
-And liars aren't called dads either.

9
00:00:26,880 --> 00:00:28,600
How late were you?
-A quarter of an hour.

10
00:00:28,720 --> 00:00:31,640
Wow, God, you're the most
irresponsible person on the planet.

11
00:00:31,720 --> 00:00:33,760
That's not true, Rotem was there and no one came to pick her up,

12
00:00:33,840 --> 00:00:35,360
so the teacher gave her to me.

13
00:00:35,480 --> 00:00:37,000
And I waited until her dad came to get her.

14
00:00:37,080 --> 00:00:39,840
Alright then, so you're the deputy of the most
irresponsible person on the planet.

15
00:00:39,920 --> 00:00:42,680
He also got a letter.
-Right.

16
00:00:42,800 --> 00:00:45,840
A letter?
-I put it in my pocket, forgot about it, because of the teacher's yelling.

17
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:48,000
What letter? What's it say?
-I don't know, I didn't open it.

18
00:00:48,560 --> 00:00:49,720
Open it, see what it is.

19
00:00:50,800 --> 00:00:51,920
"Dear parents, hello.

20
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:54,120
I regret to inform you that your child has lice.

21
00:00:56,840 --> 00:00:58,680
We ask that you address this issue urgently

22
00:00:58,800 --> 00:01:02,200
and no, your child will not be able to attend kindergarten.
Regards, Ortal the teacher."

23
00:01:04,120 --> 00:01:05,000
No way.

24
00:01:05,319 --> 00:01:07,640
Girls, girls, don't get too close to each other,
each on her own side.

25
00:01:07,960 --> 00:01:11,280
But we're playing quietly.
-Alright, each in her own section,

26
00:01:11,360 --> 00:01:13,120
don't get close. Put on some music for them.

27
00:01:13,720 --> 00:01:15,000
Too bad we don't have "Nehama the Louse."

28
00:01:15,080 --> 00:01:16,600
We don't need it, we have enough lice of our own.

29
00:01:22,440 --> 00:01:25,080
Look at me, look at me and...

30
00:01:35,040 --> 00:01:37,200
Shabbat shalom.
-Shabbat shalom, Shabbat shalom.

31
00:01:37,360 --> 00:01:39,840
As you mentioned, Shabbat shalom.

32
00:01:39,920 --> 00:01:41,080
Mentioned?
-We mentioned.

33
00:01:41,160 --> 00:01:45,800
Look how every Shabbat everyone
shifts the time however they want. We mentioned.

34
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:49,840
Where are the guests I love
to give the biggest hugs to?

35
00:01:49,960 --> 00:01:51,520
Come here.
-No, no, Mom, no hugs today.

36
00:01:52,200 --> 00:01:55,520
Why not?
-Because the guests have guests in their hair, lice.

37
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:02,680
It's nothing, it happens to everyone, everyone has it,

38
00:02:02,800 --> 00:02:04,080
it's probably from kindergarten.

39
00:02:04,160 --> 00:02:06,400
Yeah, all the little pests they bring in
from kindergarten and school.

40
00:02:06,480 --> 00:02:10,000
I wonder who the first pest was
that brought the pest to kindergarten,

41
00:02:10,080 --> 00:02:13,040
that's what's interesting.
-Who? The son of the importer of the lice shampoo.

42
00:02:13,160 --> 00:02:14,880
The daughter of the one who brings the combs!

43
00:02:15,400 --> 00:02:16,640
Girls, go to the balcony.

44
00:02:17,560 --> 00:02:18,880
Did you put something on them?

45
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:21,760
No, what, just now, on the way here
in the car, we found out they have lice.

46
00:02:21,840 --> 00:02:25,040
Did they announce it on the news?
-No, Dad, we got a letter.

47
00:02:25,120 --> 00:02:27,600
To the car?
-No, in it, it was in my pocket...

48
00:02:27,680 --> 00:02:29,960
Okay, that's not important. In it,
now we need to find a pharmacy on duty,

49
00:02:30,040 --> 00:02:32,120
buy the shampoo, and I'll comb them with the fine comb.

50
00:02:32,200 --> 00:02:33,880
Okay, forget it, Mom, I'll do it at home.

51
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:37,240
I remember, back in my day, they used to take a jar,

52
00:02:37,840 --> 00:02:40,640
they'd put in like a third vinegar,
a third oil, and a third lime.

53
00:02:41,720 --> 00:02:44,720
A louse wouldn't come out of that alive.

54
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:47,120
Neither would a person come out of that alive.

55
00:02:47,720 --> 00:02:49,400
Sorry, there are some more sophisticated treatments now.

56
00:02:49,480 --> 00:02:52,920
Yeah, and the lice are more sophisticated too.
-Are you talking about lice?

57
00:02:53,640 --> 00:02:55,520
Didn't Mom tell you Ofer is coming today?

58
00:02:55,680 --> 00:02:57,360
Ofer?
-Yeah, surprise,

59
00:02:57,680 --> 00:03:00,200
someone can come for Friday dinners
from my side of the family too.

60
00:03:00,920 --> 00:03:03,160
Of course.
-Yeah, he wanted to meet the family.

61
00:03:03,240 --> 00:03:04,760
And you want to give him lice.

62
00:03:04,840 --> 00:03:07,240
Come on, why are you making such a drama?

63
00:03:07,320 --> 00:03:11,280
What, it’s just a few lice
on the girls' heads.

64
00:03:11,840 --> 00:03:13,400
It’s not even a permanent settlement yet,

65
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:16,320
just a few trailers on some isolated hill

66
00:03:16,440 --> 00:03:18,080
and they’re still illegal.

67
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:20,640
What a pain, I’m already itching.

68
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:23,920
Itching? You haven’t even touched them.
What’s with the itching?

69
00:03:24,080 --> 00:03:25,840
It’s psychological.
-Psychosomatic.

70
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:28,240
Psycholiceomatic.

71
00:03:29,560 --> 00:03:31,120
Okay, enough, don’t upset her, she’s stressed.

72
00:03:31,680 --> 00:03:34,120
Come on, let’s handle this before her boyfriend arrives, let’s go.

73
00:03:35,040 --> 00:03:37,160
What, are you going to bring them the treatment?

74
00:03:38,440 --> 00:03:39,680
I have a brilliant idea.
-What?

75
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:42,640
Why don’t we ask Manny and Alin to bring it?
They’re probably on their way.

76
00:03:44,080 --> 00:03:46,400
So, who’s this Ofer?
-She met him online.

77
00:03:46,480 --> 00:03:47,520
Nice, so if he’s coming to visit them

78
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:49,480
this is serious, huh?
-Probably.

79
00:03:50,080 --> 00:03:52,560
What, am I hearing some doubt?
-No, of course not!

80
00:03:52,640 --> 00:03:54,800
Mom.
-Okay, look, Moshe! This isn’t right.

81
00:03:54,880 --> 00:03:56,480
If it’s that serious, why is she keeping it a secret?

82
00:03:56,560 --> 00:03:58,760
I don’t get it, she lives here,
you’ve never heard of him?

83
00:03:58,840 --> 00:04:01,800
Well, since I’m her mom
she probably doesn’t tell me.

84
00:04:02,040 --> 00:04:03,560
Alright, I’ll check it out, okay?

85
00:04:05,640 --> 00:04:07,800
I’m itching all over!

86
00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:11,360
Maybe I’ll send Shai to buy shampoo.

87
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:14,000
No, it’s too late, I’ll do something else.

88
00:04:14,080 --> 00:04:17,399
What, a grandma remedy?
-Yeah, but just so you know, it smells a bit.

89
00:04:17,480 --> 00:04:18,480
I don’t care if it smells

90
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:20,560
as long as they don’t have lice
and it doesn’t spread to me.

91
00:04:20,640 --> 00:04:21,839
Okay, I’ll make the mixture,

92
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:24,840
let’s hope Meirav’s Ofer doesn’t smell it.

93
00:04:24,920 --> 00:04:27,080
Hey, do you know which website
she found him on?

94
00:04:31,240 --> 00:04:34,760
Which site did they meet on?
-Online, what, do I know about websites?

95
00:04:36,560 --> 00:04:39,960
Where did my successful daughter
find her suitors? Online.

96
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:44,040
Listen, back in the day, you had to put in effort, you know?

97
00:04:44,120 --> 00:04:46,000
If you wanted to date a girl, it was a project.

98
00:04:46,640 --> 00:04:49,440
If you put in the effort, you’d fall in love too.

99
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:52,800
Today it’s easy, it just happens,

100
00:04:52,880 --> 00:04:54,960
it’s nothing, it’s... it’s no big deal, you know?

101
00:04:55,520 --> 00:04:57,040
Like this, for example, the...

102
00:04:57,640 --> 00:04:59,960
What do you call them? The hooks on bras,

103
00:05:01,040 --> 00:05:01,960
what’s that?

104
00:05:03,200 --> 00:05:06,360
Back then you had to invest.
There were those hooks, remember?

105
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:07,840
There was a hook like this and a hook like that.

106
00:05:08,320 --> 00:05:09,200
The hook

107
00:05:09,280 --> 00:05:11,320
Silvan, Silvan, Silvan,
that’s too much information.

108
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:13,160
Oh, that’s too much information? It’s more...

109
00:05:13,280 --> 00:05:14,760
The internet isn’t too much information.

110
00:05:15,920 --> 00:05:17,800
Not at all. The newspaper isn’t too much information

111
00:05:17,880 --> 00:05:20,320
and the gossip sea isn’t too much information.

112
00:05:21,400 --> 00:05:23,320
What do I care, tell me, for heaven's sake,

113
00:05:23,400 --> 00:05:28,320
what do I care that Bar Refaeli
has problems with Leonardo DiCaprio?

114
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:30,200
Who even cares?

115
00:05:31,200 --> 00:05:33,360
Now it turns out he’s in love with an actress

116
00:05:33,440 --> 00:05:35,160
who’s in a movie with him, you know?

117
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:40,200
Her, listen closely, he met her
before he met Bar Refaeli.

118
00:05:40,280 --> 00:05:43,320
But they talked about marriage, right?
-No, no, those are just rumors, rumors.

119
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:44,960
Forget it, it’s pointless there.

120
00:05:45,200 --> 00:05:47,040
They talked about...

121
00:05:48,400 --> 00:05:51,760
It's a mess, huh? This internet thing is a mess.

122
00:05:51,880 --> 00:05:53,280
Hey, what's up with Avi? Why isn't he answering?

123
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:55,360
Now it's ringing.

124
00:05:55,920 --> 00:05:57,480
Shabbat Shalom.

125
00:05:57,880 --> 00:06:00,160
Wait, wait, wait,
stop the girls, don't let them play together.

126
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:01,440
Is he here?

127
00:06:01,520 --> 00:06:04,880
What happened? Why not play together?
-Your girls probably have lice.

128
00:06:04,960 --> 00:06:07,680
Girls, go to the balcony.
-Oh no. Hey, again?

129
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:12,440
Enough with the lice. I'm really asking,
if possible, let's not talk about it.

130
00:06:12,920 --> 00:06:15,480
Tell me, Meirav, what did I hear? Today
some guy is coming to meet the family?

131
00:06:16,040 --> 00:06:18,360
Ofer. That's why I don't want
you to talk more about the lice,

132
00:06:18,440 --> 00:06:20,480
there are way more interesting topics
we can discuss.

133
00:06:20,560 --> 00:06:22,640
Besides, how do you know
a guy should come to me?

134
00:06:22,720 --> 00:06:24,280
Your wall on Facebook... is full of graffiti.

135
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:26,760
And we heard your blow dryer
from the room, working on turbo.

136
00:06:26,840 --> 00:06:28,400
Because your girls have lice.

137
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:31,520
So if a few happened to jump on me,
I burned them with the blow dryer.

138
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:33,640
Tell me, what... how's Ofer? What's his status?

139
00:06:33,720 --> 00:06:36,200
Job, bank account,
you like him, he likes you more,

140
00:06:36,280 --> 00:06:37,160
spill some details.

141
00:06:37,840 --> 00:06:40,840
Hey, he's coming soon, chill.

142
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:46,080
And Manny and everyone, no questions about what Manny just asked.

143
00:06:46,160 --> 00:06:49,360
A test of a good, warm, healthy family,

144
00:06:49,560 --> 00:06:51,560
and he doesn't have lice.
-What lice?

145
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:54,040
And cumin.
-Cumin?

146
00:06:54,120 --> 00:06:56,280
Have you ever seen a Persian with lice?
-No, not really.

147
00:06:56,760 --> 00:06:58,160
The lice don't like the smell.

148
00:06:59,200 --> 00:07:01,360
That's true.

149
00:07:01,440 --> 00:07:04,880
Well, Mom, that color is awful.
-Well, the color isn't really our problem.

150
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:08,280
Look, you wash the girls' hair,
you comb it with the fine comb,

151
00:07:08,360 --> 00:07:11,680
then you wash it with my shampoo,
and you quickly perfume the shower.

152
00:07:11,760 --> 00:07:13,720
Now go. Hey, come on. No time.

153
00:07:14,320 --> 00:07:16,720
What's that smell? You know Ofer is coming.

154
00:07:16,840 --> 00:07:20,200
Come on, stop making a drama out of everything.
By the time he gets here, it'll fade away.

155
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:22,640
Alright, I'm going to the girls.

156
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:24,440
Talk.

157
00:07:26,120 --> 00:07:28,320
Talk about what? What does Mom want to know?

158
00:07:28,400 --> 00:07:30,360
Tell me, how come
no one has ever heard of this Ofer?

159
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:32,880
When did you meet?
-Yesterday.

160
00:07:33,360 --> 00:07:35,480
And you already invited him?
-He wanted to come.

161
00:07:36,120 --> 00:07:37,640
Serious guy.
-Of course.

162
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:38,720
What, where did you meet?

163
00:07:39,280 --> 00:07:40,800
In some forum.
-What forum?

164
00:07:41,440 --> 00:07:43,400
"Want to start a family? Join us."

165
00:07:43,480 --> 00:07:46,560
What, are those people who gave up on getting married
and want to have a kid alone?

166
00:07:46,640 --> 00:07:49,600
I protest the use of "gave up"
but something like that.

167
00:07:49,680 --> 00:07:51,880
I don't get it, so he's coming today
to audition for our family?

168
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:55,000
No one has ever had lice, you heard?

169
00:07:55,080 --> 00:07:57,720
Did you tell that to the parents?
-I know what I'm doing.

170
00:07:57,800 --> 00:07:59,520
If the parents see they're being tested, they'll freak out,

171
00:07:59,760 --> 00:08:01,560
then he'll fall in love with them and maybe with me too.

172
00:08:01,640 --> 00:08:02,840
What are you doing to yourself? Tell me,

173
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:05,120
you realize he's not looking for a bride, right?

174
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:06,800
Is that what you want to be, a single mom?

175
00:08:07,360 --> 00:08:09,960
I'm sure I'll convince him
to stay, don't ruin this for me.

176
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:16,920
So what, Dad, excited?
-What do I have to be excited about?

177
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:19,400
Because of the groom.
-Leave it, what's there to be excited about?

178
00:08:19,520 --> 00:08:20,880
Nothing new here, believe me,

179
00:08:20,960 --> 00:08:25,240
it's the same fifty guys registered
on those fifty dating sites.

180
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:30,280
Believe me, all this internet
is a thousand fake people.

181
00:08:31,440 --> 00:08:34,320
They talk to each other like it's all made up.

182
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:37,720
Why should I even get worked up? You get it?

183
00:08:39,799 --> 00:08:42,919
No, you're right. Every pot has its lid,
even a pressure cooker.

184
00:08:43,640 --> 00:08:45,520
I don’t get it. Come on, tell me, please,

185
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:46,760
They just met yesterday,

186
00:08:47,080 --> 00:08:49,760
And now he’s already coming to meet the family. What the...

187
00:08:50,320 --> 00:08:55,320
Something smells, right?
-Yeah, yeah.

188
00:08:55,880 --> 00:08:57,960
Do you smell that?
-Could be he’s ugly.

189
00:08:58,520 --> 00:09:00,560
Ugly?
-Maybe he’s limited in some way.

190
00:09:00,640 --> 00:09:02,840
Maybe he’s blind, maybe he has one leg.

191
00:09:03,440 --> 00:09:06,320
Maybe he’s cross-eyed? Like this.

192
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:09,280
He could also be a certain kind of crazy.

193
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:11,840
Moshe! It stinks here, I’m telling you.

194
00:09:11,920 --> 00:09:15,280
Yeah, we already agreed with you.
-No, no, here, here, in the living room.

195
00:09:15,360 --> 00:09:16,480
Open up, air it out.

196
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:19,520
What’s that? Is someone dying in there?
-The lice.

197
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:21,440
Alright, I’m off to meetings.

198
00:09:23,240 --> 00:09:24,680
What, you’re done?
-Almost,

199
00:09:24,760 --> 00:09:27,480
You need to leave the stuff on their heads
so the active ingredient starts working.

200
00:09:27,560 --> 00:09:28,960
Active ingredient?
-It’s a lice thing...

201
00:09:30,560 --> 00:09:33,520
So, how does it work exactly,
the stuff you put on my girls' heads?

202
00:09:34,120 --> 00:09:36,280
If the stuff doesn’t kill the lice,

203
00:09:36,360 --> 00:09:37,760
then the smell drives them away.

204
00:09:38,040 --> 00:09:39,520
What lice? Who has lice?

205
00:09:39,880 --> 00:09:42,840
Just a few lice on Shai's girls' heads.

206
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:44,720
You don’t need to make a big deal out of everything.

207
00:09:45,560 --> 00:09:47,120
I’m going back to the shower.

208
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:48,400
What, you left them there alone?

209
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:51,320
I had to breathe a bit.
-I can’t believe it.

210
00:09:51,640 --> 00:09:54,040
What lice? You’re not worried about my girls getting infected.

211
00:09:54,120 --> 00:09:56,160
It’s fine, Mom’s taking care of it.
-But why here?

212
00:09:56,280 --> 00:09:57,560
Because, well, I didn’t have time at home,

213
00:09:57,640 --> 00:10:00,240
more like I didn’t know at home,
I found out on the way here, during the drive.

214
00:10:00,720 --> 00:10:01,960
I’m on my way here?

215
00:10:02,040 --> 00:10:05,880
Did the kindergarten teacher stop you at the intersection and tell you
or was there a sign saying "Caution, lice on heads!"?

216
00:10:05,960 --> 00:10:08,440
Well, my Shai got a letter from the teacher
and forgot it in his pocket,

217
00:10:08,520 --> 00:10:09,680
he just showed it to me now.

218
00:10:09,760 --> 00:10:13,160
Great, the main thing is you gave my Moshe
the royal title "the idiot."

219
00:10:13,240 --> 00:10:15,040
You didn’t give it to him, he earned it honestly.

220
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:17,360
Well, in the meantime, your Shai is threatening the throne.

221
00:10:19,520 --> 00:10:20,760
The smell is better.

222
00:10:21,920 --> 00:10:23,080
So, what, what are we talking about?

223
00:10:23,720 --> 00:10:27,440
Oh, Orna told me someone is coming tonight
that Meirav is dating.

224
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:30,920
Dating him... she went out once,

225
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:35,320
and he’s already coming to meet the family.
-How nice.

226
00:10:35,880 --> 00:10:37,080
There are stories like that about people

227
00:10:37,160 --> 00:10:41,480
who from the first moment say, that’s the one,
I want to meet her parents now.

228
